Class QueryServiceDaoSupport

java.lang.Object
  org.anyframe.query.dao.QueryServiceDaoSupport

public class QueryServiceDaoSupport
extends Object

This is a Wrapper class in order to use with the QueryService API easily The approaching logic for the data is handled by inheriting this class in each of the DAO class.

batchUpdate

protected int[] batchUpdate(String queryId,
                            List<?> targetList)
Issue update statement (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) using JDBC 2.0 batch updates and named parameter to set values on a dynamic Query created by this method.

Parameters:
queryId - identifier of query statement to execute
targetList - a set of variable for executing query (is the List of Object or Map)
Returns:
an array of the number of rows affected by each statement
Throws:
QueryException - if there is any problem issuing the update

protected int create(String queryId,
                     Object targetObj1,
                     Object targetObj2)
Execute the INSERT query statement using the two targetObject including the inputed value, queryId which defined in query mappings. At the execution of the appropriate query statement, first, the targetObject's variable name adds 1 to the defined variableNmae(default='vo'), the second targetObject's variable name adds 2 to the defined variableName.

Parameters:
queryId - identifier of query statement to execute
targetObj1 - The first object including the needed input value at the query execution
targetObj2 - The second object including the needed input value at the query execution
Returns:
the number of rows affected
Throws:
QueryException - if there is any problem executing the query
